<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Yes. If lfs->cfg->cache_size is smaller than the requested new file size, the memcpy can write past the destination buffer. Example: configure lfs->cfg->cache_size = 16 and lfs->inline_max = 32, then call lfs_file_truncate_(..., size = 32). The code takes the inline branch (size <= inline_max), sets file->cache.size = lfs->cfg->cache_size (16) but then calls memcpy(file->cache.buffer, lfs->rcache.buffer, size) copying 32 bytes into a buffer only known to be cache_size bytes long — this can overflow file->cache.buffer (and/or rcache.buffer if it is smaller), violating Rule 21.17.
</scenario>
